properties.remarks: Accumulated mainly on a deck surface. Snow was falling the heaviest around 4 AM.
6 hour observation at the office. There was one inch exactly on grassy surfaces.
Overnight snowfall estimate from X post.
Public Safety official reached out to officers and they measured 5.0 inches of snow so far in Unalaska. Blowing snow has caused significantly reduced visibility. It is still snowing currently.
Several reports of snow in excess of 10 inches between 4 PM April 16 and the report time at Big Sky Resort, including a peak report of 14 inches at Lookout Ridge.
Snotel equipment at Shower Falls estimates 15 inches new snow over the 12 hours prior to report time.
